    {
      "id": "8b8b06e8-6dc6-4d37-961f-79cf55166f96",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Exercise 2: Write a function is_BST to check if the input root node is the root of a BST\n\n\nTest cases:\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> n2 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(2, \n        new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(1, null, null),\n        new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(6, new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(4, null, null), null));\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> n9 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(9, \n        new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(7, null, null), null),\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> root_1 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(5, n2, n9);\n\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> m2 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(2, \n        new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(1, null, null),\n        new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(4, new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(3, null, null), null));\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> m9 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(9, \n        new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(7, null, null), null);\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> root_2 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(5, m2, m9);\n\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> tmp_1 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(5, \n        BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(6, null, null), \n        BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(8, null, null));\n\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> tmp_2 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(5, \n        BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(2, null, null), \n        BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(3, null, null));\n\n    System.out.println(is_BST(n2) == true);\n    System.out.println(is_BST(n9) == true);\n    System.out.println(is_BST(root_1) == false);\n    System.out.println(is_BST(root_2) == true);\n    System.out.println(is_BST(tmp_1) == false);\n    System.out.println(is_BST(tmp_2) == false);\n\n",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "8b8b06e8-6dc6-4d37-961f-79cf55166f96"
      }
