      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Exercise 4: Implement the insertion method to insert a new key into a BST",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "2f87fa80-0865-4897-9d9a-0e9bb08714e4"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "bf1a7ec5-c626-4bdf-8afb-fd0a04c307c2",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "public BinaryTreeNode<Integer> insert_(BinaryTreeNode<Integer> origin_root, Integer key){\r\n        if(origin_root == null){\r\n            return new BinaryTreeNode<>(key, null, null);\r\n        }\r\n        else{\r\n            if(origin_root.key.equals(key)){\r\n                IO.print(\"Duplicate key\");\r\n            }\r\n            if(origin_root.key.compareTo(key)>0){\r\n                origin_root.left= insert_(origin_root.left,key);\r\n            }\r\n            if(origin_root.key.compareTo(key)<0){\r\n                origin_root.right =  insert_(origin_root.right,key);\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        return origin_root;\r\n\r\n    }\r\n    public void insert(Integer key){\r\n        root = insert_(root, key);\r\n    }",
